Returns up-state, aka. `|0>`, +Z eigenstate:

$$
|0\rangle = \begin{pmatrix}
1 \\ 0
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Returns down-state, aka. `|1>`, -Z eigenstate:

$$
|1\rangle = \begin{pmatrix}
0 \\ 1
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Returns plus-state, aka. `|+>`, +X eigenstate:

$$
|+\rangle = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \begin{pmatrix}
1 \\ 1
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Returns minus-state, aka. `|->`, -X eigenstate:

$$
|-\rangle = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \begin{pmatrix}
1 \\ -1
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Returns yplus-state, aka. `|y+>`, +Y eigenstate:

$$
|y+\rangle = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \begin{pmatrix}
1 \\ i
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Returns yplus-state, aka. `|y->`, -Y eigenstate:

$$
|y-\rangle = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \begin{pmatrix}
1 \\ -i
\end{pmatrix}
$$

Rx(pi / 2).

$$
X^{\frac{1}{2}} =
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\begin{bmatrix}
1  & - i \\
- i & 1
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Ry(pi / 2).

$$
Y^{\frac{1}{2}} =
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & - 1 \\
1 & 1
\end{bmatrix}
$$

Rz(pi / 2).

$$
Z^{\frac{1}{2}} =
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\begin{bmatrix}
1 - i & 0 \\
0 & 1 + i
\end{bmatrix}
$$

R\[X + Y\](pi / 2).

$$
W^{\frac{1}{2}} =
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\begin{bmatrix}
1 & -\sqrt{i} \\
\sqrt{-i} & 1
\end{bmatrix}
$$
